1.00	Geraldo_brawl	Geraldo (TV series)	Geraldo is an American daytime television talk show hosted by Geraldo Rivera that aired in syndication from September 7, 1987, to June 12, 1998. On the last two seasons, it was known as The Geraldo Rivera Show. Both titles were produced by Investigative News Group in association with Tribune Entertainment. In addition, the show was co-distributed with Paramount Domestic Television from 1987-1988, followed by King World Productions from 1995-1998. The latter two companies are now known as CBS Television Distribution.	
